Create an abstract BaseBloc<Event, State> class that extends Bloc<Event, State>:
1. Implement common error handling mechanisms
2. Add lifecycle management methods
3. Include logging capabilities for debugging
4. Provide helper methods for common BLoC operations
5. Ensure compatibility with existing flutter_bloc patterns

Example implementation:
```dart
abstract class BaseBloc<E, S> extends Bloc<E, S> {
  BaseBloc(S initialState) : super(initialState) {
    on<E>(_eventHandler);
  }

  Future<void> _eventHandler(E event, Emitter<S> emit) async {
    try {
      await mapEventToState(event, emit);
    } catch (error, stackTrace) {
      handleError(error, stackTrace);
      emit(createErrorState(error, state));
    }
  }

  Future<void> mapEventToState(E event, Emitter<S> emit);

  void handleError(dynamic error, StackTrace stackTrace) {
    // Default error handling logic
    log('Error in ${runtimeType.toString()}: $error');
    log(stackTrace.toString());
  }

  S createErrorState(dynamic error, S currentState);
}
```

Create a mixin or base class for state objects using freezed:
1. Define common state properties (isLoading, error, isSuccess)
2. Implement helper methods for state transitions
3. Create factory constructors for common state types
4. Ensure serialization/deserialization support

Example implementation:
```dart
@freezed
abstract class BaseState with _$BaseState {
  const factory BaseState({
    @Default(false) bool isLoading,
    @Default(false) bool isSuccess,
    Object? error,
  }) = _BaseState;

  const BaseState._();

  bool get hasError => error != null;

  BaseState loading() => copyWith(isLoading: true, error: null, isSuccess: false);
  BaseState success() => copyWith(isLoading: false, error: null, isSuccess: true);
  BaseState failure(Object error) => copyWith(isLoading: false, error: error, isSuccess: false);
}
```

