Design and implement a standard event pattern:
1. Create a base event interface or abstract class
2. Define common event categories (init, refresh, load, submit, etc.)
3. Implement helper methods for event creation
4. Use freezed for immutable event classes

Example implementation:
```dart
@freezed
abstract class BaseEvent with _$BaseEvent {
  const factory BaseEvent.init() = InitEvent;
  const factory BaseEvent.refresh() = RefreshEvent;
  const factory BaseEvent.load({required String id}) = LoadEvent;
  const factory BaseEvent.submit({required Map<String, dynamic> data}) = SubmitEvent;
  const factory BaseEvent.error({required Object error}) = ErrorEvent;
}
```

